Intervention: All participants in the study, PA compression image set
All image sets (30 sets of patient-assisted compression images) were evaluated to determine the acceptability of overall clinical image quality by two (2) readers.
All study participants, TC Compression Image Sets
All image sets (30 sets of TC compression images) were evaluated to determine the acceptability of the overall quality of the clinical image by two (2) readers.
Eligibility: Women are 40 years of age or older;
Are asymptomatic and programmed for FFDM screening mammography;
Have breast sizes compatible with the dimensions of an image detector of 24 x 31 cm, without anatomical cut;
Are documented as non-pregnant on the basis of the investigator's medical judgement and taking into account local clinical practice standards for proof of non-pregnantness;
Be able and willing to comply with study procedures; and
Be able and willing to provide written informed consent to participate.
Have already been included in this study or are participating in another study that should interfere with the procedures or results of the study;

• have undergone diagnostic or surgical procedures or breast interventions, including breast biopsy, lumpectomy or reconstruction, within five (5) years (five years) from the date of the study review;
In the course of radiation therapy or chemotherapy, or with a history of prior radiation therapy on either breast;
Results: Number of subjects with an overall clinical image quality acceptable for patient-assisted (PA) and technologist-controlled (TC) image sets

A set of PA images and a set of TC images were acquired from each filled subject. The overall acceptability of clinical image quality was collected and summarized on a subject-by-subject basis using acceptable or unacceptable binary responses for two-way PA and TC compression image sets. Two readers evaluated each of the 60 sets of images (30 PA and 30 sets of TC compression images from 30 completed participants).
Time limit: By completing the study, on average 1 month
Title of the arm/group: All participants in the study, PA compression image set
All image sets (30 sets of images with patient-assisted compression) were evaluated by two (2) readers to determine the acceptability of the overall quality of the clinical image.
Type of measure: Number of participants
Title of the arm/group: All participants in the study, TC Compression Image Sets
All image sets (30 sets of TC compression images) were evaluated by two (2) readers to determine the acceptability of the overall quality of the clinical image.
Type of measure: Number of participants
